Subject: Re: [VB] ignition wiring

> Hi Folks,
> Is there an easy way to remove the ignition switch on a 60 DC?
> I had it stolen, they yanked the wires, hot wired it and went for a ride.  I
> have it back now, but need to re-do the ignition wires.
> I have seen the diagram, but can not work behind the odometer crown.
> 
> Any suggestions?

Remove the set screw in the "crown" below the switch & take the switch out,
install the wires per the diagram, reinstall the switch & set screw & you
are done.

Tom
63 DC
